        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 3:36AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 334 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jerusalem, or 19 miles northeast of Russellville, moving northeast at
40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brock Creek Campground...         Rupert...
Scotland...                       Cleveland...
Pleasant Valley in Pope County... Broomfield...
Dabney...                         Crabtree...
Solo...                           Caglesville...
Mountain Man Trailhead...         Oak Grove in Pope County...
Beverage Town...                  Augsburg...
Jerusalem...                      Woolum...
Chimes...                         Dover...
Hector...                         Nogo...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
